Export sq objects into other formats

Source: R/export_sq.R
export_sq.Rd

Convert object of class sq to another class from another package. Currently supported packages are ape with its formats (AAbin and DNAbin), Bioconductor (AAStringSet, DNAStringSet) and seqinr (SeqFastaAA, SeqFastadna).

export_sq(sq, export_format, name)

Arguments

sq

a sq object.
export_format

a character string indicating package and the destination class; it should be one of the following: "seqinr::SeqFastaAA", "ape::AAbin", "Biostrings::AAStringSet", "seqinr::SeqFastadna", "ape::DNAbin", "Biostrings::DNAStringSet".
name

a character vector of length equal to sq length.

See also

sq import_sq

Examples

sq_ami <- construct_sq(c("MVVGL", "LAVPP"))
export_sq(sq_ami, "ape::AAbin")
#> Error: you need to install 'ape' package to export object to its formats
export_sq(sq_ami, "Biostrings::AAStringSet", c("one", "two"))
#> Error: you need to install 'Biostrings' package to export object to its formats
export_sq(sq_ami, "seqinr::SeqFastaAA")
#> Error: you need to install 'seqinr' package to export object to its formats

sq_dna <- construct_sq(c("TGATGAAGCGCA", "TTGATGGGAA"))
export_sq(sq_dna, "ape::DNAbin", name = c("one", "two"))
#> Error: you need to install 'ape' package to export object to its formats
export_sq(sq_dna, "Biostrings::DNAStringSet")
#> Error: you need to install 'Biostrings' package to export object to its formats
export_sq(sq_dna, "seqinr::SeqFastadna")
#> Error: you need to install 'seqinr' package to export object to its formats
